  "result": "Build is green. Confirmed eprintln was removed from base.rs and only warnings remain.\n\n**Root cause:** `crates/lua-stdlib/src/state_stub.rs:1197` — `load_with_reader` propagated reader errors via `?` instead of catching them. C-Lua wraps the parser in `luaD_protectedparser` so reader errors become `(nil, error_message)` returned from `load`, not a raised Lua error. The first reader-error-returning call in calls.lua is line 322 (`assert(not load(function () return true end))`), which expected `load` to return failure but instead saw the error escape up to the top-level `pcall_k`.\n\n**Fix:** In `load_with_reader`, catch `LuaError` from the reader, push the error's payload (string) onto the stack, and return `Ok(false)` so `load_aux` produces the canonical `(nil, msg)` return values.\n\n**New state:** Build green. The test now progresses past the original failure point: it now fails at calls.lua:332 (`assert(type(f) == \"function\" and f() == 1)`), a different bug in the `string.dump`/`load(..., \"b\", ...)` binary-chunk path — out of scope for this fix.",
